HEADWORD: Hamburg
<hw>Ham"burg</hw> <pr>(-b⟦ucir⟧rg)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A commercial
city of Germany, near the mouth of the Elbe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Black Hamburg grape</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Black</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Hamburg edging</b></col>, <cd>a kind of
embroidered work done by machinery on cambric or muslin; -- used for
trimming.</cd> -- <col><b>Hamburg lake</b></col>, <cd>a purplish crimson
pigment resembling cochineal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hame</ent>⟦br⟧
